value.title: Angel dad slams Joe Biden's immigration orders: 'Insanity on steroids'
value.excerpt: A California father, whose son was killed in a car accident with an illegal immigrant slammed President Joe Biden’s move to halt deportations of undocumented migrants on Friday, calling the administration's actions “insanity on steroids.”

value.title: Biden administration’s CBP revives ‘catch and release’ policy at border amid COVID concerns
value.excerpt: A perfect storm of events has the Biden administration’s Customs and Border Protection on its heels in parts of Texas.

value.title: Pence will be ‘very active’ in 2022 elections amid new partnerships with conservative groups: ex-VP's adviser
value.excerpt: Pence announced he is joining the Heritage Foundation as a distinguished fellow and is also entering into a partnership with the conservative Young America’s Foundation.

value.title: Biden flying to Delaware despite CDC warnings to avoid travel
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to travel to Delaware this weekend, in what will be his first out-of-town trip since taking office, despite warnings from the Centers of Disease Control and Prevention to avoid travel.

value.title: Pence joining Heritage Foundation as distinguished fellow
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence is joining the Heritage Foundation, one of the oldest and most influential think tanks in the conservative movement.

value.title: Trump resigns from Screen Actors Guild: ‘I no longer wish to be associated with your union’
value.excerpt: President Trump is resigning from the Screen Actors Guild - American Federation of Television and Radio Artists after they threatened to expel his membership from the union after the Capitol riot -- to which he said, “Who cares!”

value.title: Biden addresses National Prayer Breakfast, says 'we need to defeat political extremism'
value.excerpt: President Biden addressed the National Prayer Breakfast on Thursday, saying the country needs to "defeat political extremism" and rely on "faith to guide us out of the darkness and into the light" amid the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Maxine Waters says Trump should be charged with 'premeditated murder'
value.excerpt: Democratic Rep. Maxine Waters of California Tuesday said she thinks former President Donald Trump should be charged with "premeditated murder" over the deadly riots at the U.S. Capitol on Jan. 6.

value.title: USA Today column argues Tom Brady has gotten 'undeserved pass' for supporting Trump, cites 'white privilege'
value.excerpt: With Tom Brady days away from playing in his tenth Super Bowl, a USA Today sports columnist has taken aim at the NFL superstar over his past support of former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Psaki defends Biden's 'vast majority' are 'decent' comments about FBI agents
value.excerpt: The White House doubled down on President Biden’s remarks Tuesday saying that a “vast majority” of law enforcement officers were “decent, honorable people” after two FBI agents were killed in the line of duty.

value.title: Psaki's resurfaced tweets slam Trump, Sanders supporters, severely undercutting 'unity' message
value.excerpt: President Biden often invoked a message of national unity on the 2020 campaign trail and since taking office last month – but did his top spokesperson get the message?

value.title: Iranian resistance leader says regime 'at its weakest point,' urges Biden to hold it to account
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: The leader of the main Iranian resistance group tells Fox News that the regime in Tehran is at its "weakest point" in its history, and is calling on the Biden administration to hold the regime accountable for its human rights violations.

value.title: Biden says ‘no one in our family’ will be involved in government decisions
value.excerpt: President Biden said he intends to keep his family and his administration separate as reports surrounding the business dealings of his son and brother raised questions of potential impropriety.

value.title: Sen. Kennedy blasts 'immeasurably foolish' Biden orders that will 'gut Louisiana like a fish'
value.excerpt: Sen. John Kennedy, R-La., warned Tuesday that President Biden's sweeping executive orders related to the industrial energy sector and immigration will be detrimental to both the nation and, in the former case, his home state.

value.title: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot blames Trump for standoff between city’s public schools and teachers union
value.excerpt: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot on Tuesday blamed the impasse between the city’s public schools and teachers union on President Donald Trump for not being able to roll out a nationwide vaccine program while he was in office.

value.title: Sen. Kaine sets aside Trump censure resolution: 'There's not enough support on either side'
value.excerpt: Sens. Tim Kaine and Susan Collins have set aside the bipartisan effort to censure former President Trump for his role in the Jan. 6 Capitol riot for lack of support from both Democrats and Republicans.

value.title: Graham urges acting AG to 'refrain from interfering' in Durham, Hunter Biden probes amid Garland confirmation
value.excerpt: Sen. Lindsey Graham, the top Republican on the Senate Judiciary Committee, on Tuesday urged acting Attorney General Monty Wilkinson to "refrain from interfering" in Special Counsel John Durham’s investigation and the federal investigation into Hunter Biden’s "tax affairs" while the Senate works to confirm

value.title: Senate approves Pete Buttigieg as Biden's transportation secretary
value.excerpt: Pete Buttigieg, known throughout his 2020 presidential bid as "Mayor Pete," got a big promotion Tuesday to become President Biden's next transportation secretary.

value.title: Biden's Keystone XL pipeline cancellation is gut punch to small businesses
value.excerpt: While opponents of the long-controversial Keystone XL Pipeline cheered its cancellation by President Biden's administration, others like Nebraska truck driver Chris Olsen shook their heads in dismay.

value.title: New DOJ hire is former colleague of Hunter Biden defense attorney
value.excerpt: The newly selected acting head of the Justice Department's criminal division is a former colleague of the attorney now representing Hunter Biden in the face of a DOJ investigation.

value.title: Live Updates: Biden meets with Republican senators on coronavirus aid
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Monday night said that he's unwilling to settle on an insufficient coronavirus aid package.

value.title: Ex-NFL star Marcellus Wiley calls for 'separate transgender category' in school sports after Biden order
value.excerpt: Former NFL star and current Fox Sports 1 host Marcellus Wiley called last week for the creation of a "separate transgender category" for youth athletics.

value.title: Biden administration cites climate change as a 'racial justice issue'
value.excerpt: Climate Adviser Gina McCarthy explained that challenges are exacerbated in communities that haven't been invested in.

value.title: Howard Kurtz: Media will use impeachment trial to ‘convict Donald Trump in the court of public opinion’
value.excerpt: Fox News media analyst Howard Kurtz predicts Donald Trump’s second impeachment trial will be “grand political theater” that will dominate media coverage.

value.title: Biden State Dept. spokeswoman called police 'largest threat to US national security': Report
value.excerpt: Jalina Porter, who has been named deputy spokesperson for the U.S. State Department under President Biden, wrote that U.S. cops posed the largest national security threat because of attacks against Blacks

value.title: Ukraine's Zelensky 'offended' by media reporting that Trump 'put pressure' on him
value.excerpt: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signaled that he was more upset about the aftermath of his now-infamous July 2019 phone call with then-President Donald Trump than the actual call.

value.title: Trump residency at Mar-a-Lago under Palm Beach legal review
value.excerpt: Palm Beach, Fla., officials are conducting a legal review into former President Donald Trump's residency at Mar-a-Lago, Fox News confirmed Monday.

value.title: David Schoen: What to know about Trump impeachment defense attorney
value.excerpt: High-profile civil rights attorney David Schoen, who before Jeffrey Epstein's death was in discussions to join his legal team, will be one of the two top members of former President Donald Trump's legal team for his impeachment trial, which is set to start in earnest in the Senate next week.

value.title: Kudlow: Trump was 'consequential, brilliant' president on policy
value.excerpt: New Fox Business host Larry Kudlow said Monday that former President Donald Trump would go down as a "brilliant, consequential" president on policy terms and would have been better served to focus on his achievements instead of fighting the election result in the final weeks of his term.

value.title: Kinzinger launches new PAC to 'take back' GOP from Trump
value.excerpt: Under fire by many in his own party for his vote to impeach then-President Trump, Republican Rep. Adam Kinzinger of Illinois is fighting to "take back" the GOP.
